  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Massive ascites is usually controlled over several weeks pre-operatively in liver transplant
      recipients with the risk of encephalopathy and peritonitis. We hypothesized that
      intra-operative drainage of ascites will be safe and avoids the inherent risks of
      pre-operative drainage.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
